\[02/05\]  
Purpose    
Accountability in a team setting means every member understands their responsibilities and is willing to be answerable for their actions and results.  
Positive impact of accountability  
Teams with high accountability show a 50% higher performance level than those without. They achieve targets consistently and drive growth.  
Negative Impact of lack of accountability  
Teams lacking accountability can see project failure rates increase by up to 30%, leading to missed deadlines and decreased morale.  
\[03/05\]  
How to See Accountability in Teams  
1\. Consistent achievement of goals  
Team members regularly meet or exceed their targets.  
2\. Proactive communication  
Individuals frequently update the team on their progress and challenges without prompting.  
3\. Ownership of outcomes  
Team members readily accept responsibility for the results of their actions, both good and bad.  
\[04/05\]  
Signs of Lack of Accountability  
1\. Blame shifting  
Team members blame others or external factors when things go wrong without reflecting on their contributions to the issue.  
2\. Inconsistent deliverables  
Tasks and projects are often incomplete or not delivered on time.  
3\. Avoidance of responsibility  
Individuals are reluctant to commit to tasks or are often looking for ways to offload responsibilities.  
\[05/05\]  
conclusion

Utilizing this checklist allows leaders to quickly identify areas where accountability is strong and where it may need reinforcement. Addressing "No" responses with targeted actions can help build a more accountable and high-performing team.
